      "content": "Your doctor is right about consistency, but doubling the dose is a dangerous misconception; it won't magically balance the missed dose. Your body doesn't process medication in a linear fashion, so overloading it now is riskier than a slight gap. Just take your usual 20mg dose now, and then stick strictly to tomorrow's schedule. If you are really concerned about a spike, a quick, non-emergency check-in with a nurse line is the best move.",
